[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | This script creates an output directory (defaults to `lunar_lander_output/`, see
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | the --outdir flag) with the following files:
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | 
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |     - archive.csv: The CSV representation of the final archive, obtained with

[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |     - archive_ccdf.png: A plot showing the (unnormalized) complementary

[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |       each objective p on the x-axis, this plot shows the number of
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |       solutions that had an objective of at least p.
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |     - heatmap.png: A heatmap showing the performance of solutions in the
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |       archive.
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |     - metrics.json: Metrics about the run, saved as a mapping from the metric

[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | 
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | In evaluation mode (--run-eval flag), the script will read in the archive from

[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | 
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | Usage:
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |     # Basic usage - should take ~1 hour with 4 cores.

[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | The sphere function in this example is adapted from Section 4 of Fontaine 2020
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | (https://arxiv.org/abs/1912.02400). Namely, each solution value is clipped to
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | the range [-5.12, 5.12], and the optimum is moved from [0,..] to [0.4 * 5.12 =
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | 2.048,..]. Furthermore, the objectives are normalized to the range [0,
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | 100] where 100 is the maximum and corresponds to 0 on the original sphere
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | function.
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | 
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | There are two measures in this example. The first is the sum of the first n/2
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | clipped values of the solution, and the second is the sum of the last n/2
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | clipped values of the solution. Having each measure depend equally on several
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | values in the solution space makes the problem more difficult (refer to
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | Fontaine 2020 for more info).
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | 
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | The supported algorithms are:
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | - `map_elites`: GridArchive with GaussianEmitter.
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | - `line_map_elites`: GridArchive with IsoLineEmitter.
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | - `cvt_map_elites`: CVTArchive with GaussianEmitter.
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | - `line_cvt_map_elites`: CVTArchive with IsoLineEmitter.

[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | - `cma_me_imp`: GridArchive with EvolutionStrategyEmitter using

[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | - `cma_me_rd`: GridArchive with EvolutionStrategyEmitter using

[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |   TwoStageRandomDirectionRanker and mu selection rule.
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | - `cma_me_opt`: GridArchive with EvolutionStrategyEmitter using ObjectiveRanker
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |   with mu selection rule.
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | - `cma_me_mixed`: GridArchive with EvolutionStrategyEmitter, where half (7) of

[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | - `cma_mega`: GridArchive with GradientArborescenceEmitter.
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | - `cma_mega_adam`: GridArchive with GradientArborescenceEmitter using Adam
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |   Optimizer.
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | - `cma_mae`: GridArchive (learning_rate = 0.01) with EvolutionStrategyEmitter
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |   using ImprovementRanker.
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | - `cma_maega`: GridArchive (learning_rate = 0.01) with
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |   GradientArborescenceEmitter using ImprovementRanker.
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | 
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | All algorithms use 15 emitters, each with a batch size of 37. Each one runs for
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | 4500 iterations for a total of 15 * 37 * 4500 ~= 2.5M evaluations.
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | 
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | Notes:
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | - `cma_mega` and `cma_mega_adam` use only one emitter and run for 10,000
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |   iterations. This is to be consistent with the paper (`Fontaine 2021
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |   <https://arxiv.org/abs/2106.03894>`_) in which these algorithms were proposed.
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | - `cma_mae` and `cma_maega` run for 10,000 iterations as well.
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | - CVTArchive in this example uses 10,000 cells, as opposed to the 250,000
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |   (500x500) in the GridArchive, so it is not fair to directly compare
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |   `cvt_map_elites` and `line_cvt_map_elites` to the other algorithms.
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | 
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | Outputs are saved in the `sphere_output/` directory by default. The archive is
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | saved as a CSV named `{algorithm}_{dim}_archive.csv`, while snapshots of the
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | heatmap are saved as `{algorithm}_{dim}_heatmap_{iteration}.png`. Metrics about
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | the run are also saved in `{algorithm}_{dim}_metrics.json`, and plots of the
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | metrics are saved in PNG's with the name `{algorithm}_{dim}_metric_name.png`.
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | 
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | To generate a video of the heatmap from the heatmap images, use a tool like
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | ffmpeg. For example, the following will generate a 6FPS video showing the
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | heatmap for cma_me_imp with 20 dims.
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | 
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |     ffmpeg -r 6 -i "sphere_output/cma_me_imp_20_heatmap_%*.png" \
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |         sphere_output/cma_me_imp_20_heatmap_video.mp4
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | 
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | Usage (see sphere_main function for all args or run `python sphere.py --help`):
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |     python sphere.py ALGORITHM
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | Example:
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |     python sphere.py map_elites
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | 
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |     # To make numpy and sklearn run single-threaded, set env variables for BLAS

[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   | Help:
[832d6524-3a4a-461d-adbd-6af28286c1cc/docs      ]   |     python sphere.py --help
